The heads were completely rebuilt right before I bought the bus. About 13,000
miles ago. They are in really good condition. I pulled the engine to correct
the end thrust so that is getting taken care of. I agree the heads should be
done right but I don't think there is much to do on these. This is Idaho so
money is a bit different here. I got a quote for $120 from another shop to do
everything you mentioned. They were jerks though so I am going to go with the
other guy. Thank you for the input though. It is always appreciated.

